WEBVTT

00:05.271 --> 00:07.206
(THUNDER CRASHING)

00:07.208 --> 00:08.907
<i>♪</i>

00:21.588 --> 00:23.088
(SCREAMING)

00:23.090 --> 00:24.757
<i>♪</i>

00:34.934 --> 00:37.503
(BATS SCREECHING)

00:39.272 --> 00:41.907
(LOUD RAP BEATS PLAYING)

00:44.744 --> 00:46.412
Whoa.

00:48.748 --> 00:50.883
Mmm. Pure pus gel.

00:50.885 --> 00:53.652
It may pass!
(KNOCKING)

00:57.891 --> 01:00.325
(LOUD ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

01:00.393 --> 01:03.962
Dude, those flies really
know how to party.

01:03.964 --> 01:06.298
We brought cake!

01:06.300 --> 01:08.000
(BOTH GRUNTS)

01:08.468 --> 01:10.803
Well, it's the thought
that counts.

01:10.805 --> 01:12.304
Mavis, why we gotta be
on lookout duty

01:12.306 --> 01:15.274
when nobody ever checks
into this room? Ever.

01:15.276 --> 01:18.043
True, but you can
never be too careful.

01:18.045 --> 01:20.379
If Aunt Lydia found us,
she'd freak right out.

01:20.381 --> 01:22.314
<i>♪ Freak right out,</i>
<i>freak right out</i>

01:22.316 --> 01:25.050
<i>♪ I'm really freaky,</i>
<i>Wendy's freaky! ♪</i>

01:25.052 --> 01:26.351
Holy rabies!

01:26.353 --> 01:27.052
Look at the time!

01:27.054 --> 01:29.621
I'm supposed to pre-slime
all the hotel room keys!

01:29.623 --> 01:32.724
Ah! Aunt Lydia promised,
next time I mess up,

01:32.726 --> 01:35.627
we'd all be ground
into zombie meat.

01:36.162 --> 01:38.597
(BOTH WHIMPERING)

01:40.834 --> 01:44.269
Mavis, I expect everything
to be perfect!

01:44.271 --> 01:48.474
It's not every day
Cornelius Shivers visits us.

01:48.476 --> 01:50.909
Really? Him! Get out!

01:50.911 --> 01:52.778
I have no idea
who that is.

01:52.780 --> 01:57.549
He only wrote
the most romantic novel
of all time,

01:57.551 --> 01:59.618
<i>A Scare To Remember!</i>

01:59.620 --> 02:01.286
(SCREAMING)

02:01.288 --> 02:05.124
Nobody captures
the romance of
undead souls

02:05.126 --> 02:10.229
screaming together
in agony
like Cornelius.

02:10.231 --> 02:11.263
(SIGHING)

02:11.265 --> 02:13.065
What...
What's wrong with her?

02:13.067 --> 02:14.800
Is she sick?
Are you sick?

02:14.802 --> 02:17.436
Do I get to be
in charge
of the hotel?

02:17.438 --> 02:19.571
(CLUCKING)
(MARIACHI BAND PLAYING)

02:20.273 --> 02:21.573
Lydia!

02:21.575 --> 02:24.476
(GASPING)
Cornelius.

02:25.111 --> 02:28.113
Yes! Saved by the...
Cockroach.

02:28.715 --> 02:30.149
Oh, the time has come

02:30.151 --> 02:32.784
to crank out
another best seller.

02:32.786 --> 02:35.487
I presume
my usual room is ready?

02:35.489 --> 02:36.555
(NERVOUS
GIRLISH GIGGLING)

02:36.557 --> 02:40.826
Book's due in two days, yeah,
but I'm not sweatin'.

02:40.828 --> 02:45.230
All I need
is good ol' room 1313.

02:45.232 --> 02:46.398
(GASPING)

02:46.400 --> 02:49.034
(LAUGHING)
Oh, yes!

02:49.435 --> 02:52.204
Code rainbow.
Code rainbow!
(GRUNTS)

02:52.206 --> 02:55.374
Make way!
Coming through!

03:01.648 --> 03:02.648
(GRUNTS)

03:02.650 --> 03:04.016
Code rainbow!

03:04.018 --> 03:05.450
(SCREAMING)

03:05.452 --> 03:08.387
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)
AUNT LYDIA: Don't worry.

03:08.389 --> 03:10.889
No monster has set a claw
or wing in the room

03:10.891 --> 03:12.424
since the last time
you were here,

03:12.426 --> 03:15.794
when you wrote
<i>Honeymoon in Hades.</i>

03:15.796 --> 03:19.298
Good, good!
I can't stand change.

03:19.300 --> 03:20.232
Even the slightest
little bit

03:20.234 --> 03:24.570
can mess up
my creative pus.
(BELL DINGS)

03:24.572 --> 03:26.071
AUNT LYDIA: Ooh!

03:26.073 --> 03:27.472
Holy rabies!

03:27.474 --> 03:31.643
Aunt Lydia, I think
I should warn you
that, um...

03:32.779 --> 03:36.648
No! Everything is
perfectly fine?

03:36.650 --> 03:37.182
Lydia,

03:37.184 --> 03:42.254
as a token of
my appreciation for
all you've done,

03:42.256 --> 03:45.891
I'm dedicating
my new book to you.

03:45.893 --> 03:49.328
(STUTTERING)
Dedication?

03:49.330 --> 03:50.696
Yeah, that's right.

03:50.698 --> 03:54.132
To me? Oh! (SIGHS)

03:54.134 --> 03:54.900
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

03:54.902 --> 03:58.770
We really dodged
a sunbeam last night.

03:58.772 --> 04:00.672
How'd you guys clean up
that room so fast?

04:00.674 --> 04:04.810
We had a little help...
From the Trash Mouth!

04:04.812 --> 04:06.812
<i>Looks like DeMar threw</i>
<i>a raging party</i>

04:06.814 --> 04:11.083
<i>and now Mom and Dad</i>
<i>are coming home early.</i>
<i>Busted!</i>

04:11.085 --> 04:14.086
<i>Well, DeMar, turn</i>
<i>that frown upside down</i>

04:14.088 --> 04:18.991
<i>'cause it's time</i>
<i>to take out</i>
<i>the Trash... Mouth!</i>

04:18.993 --> 04:20.125
<i>Simply unroll the Trash Mouth</i>

04:20.127 --> 04:21.692
<i>and watch your problems</i>
<i>get eaten away!</i>

04:21.695 --> 04:27.866
Get that gah-bage outta here
and into my trash mouth!

04:29.736 --> 04:30.936
(BELCHING)

04:30.938 --> 04:31.870
Good ol' Trashy.

04:31.872 --> 04:35.440
I gotta say, I really
thought you were done
for this time.

04:35.442 --> 04:37.876
(LAUGHING)
Never a doubt.

04:37.878 --> 04:39.611
(CORNELIUS SCREAMING)

04:39.613 --> 04:43.548
Who's to say that wasn't
a scream of delight?

04:45.918 --> 04:47.119
Okay, what just happened?

04:47.121 --> 04:48.920
Nothing!
That's the problem!

04:48.922 --> 04:52.190
I come to
Hotel Transylvania,
stay in room 1313,

04:52.192 --> 04:56.061
go to sleep, and when
I wake up, book's written.

04:56.063 --> 04:59.665
Hmm... It's like
there's something wrong
with the room.

04:59.667 --> 05:01.733
Like it's changed somehow.

05:01.735 --> 05:04.069
No, no, no, no, no.
No. No way. No.

05:04.071 --> 05:06.204
No one has touched this
room since you were here,

05:06.206 --> 05:07.572
especially us!
So, forget that!

05:07.574 --> 05:09.708
(WHISPERING)
That was so believable.

05:09.710 --> 05:12.611
This is bad,
this is really bad.

05:12.613 --> 05:13.345
What am I going to do?

05:13.347 --> 05:16.915
The publisher
wants the novel
first thing tomorrow!

05:16.917 --> 05:20.419
And I can't do it
without Maggie!

05:20.421 --> 05:21.887
Uh, what's a Maggie?

05:21.889 --> 05:24.489
Maggie is the ghost writer
who lives in the room

05:24.491 --> 05:27.893
<i>and does all the work</i>
<i>while I sleep.</i>
<i>(TYPEWRITER CLACKING)</i>

05:27.895 --> 05:30.262
Is there anything
more romantic

05:30.264 --> 05:34.599
than being stretched out
on a torture rack together?

05:34.601 --> 05:35.567
Well, I never told anyone

05:35.569 --> 05:38.937
'cause I don't want to admit
I don't know how to write.

05:38.939 --> 05:40.872
I am just a cockroach.

05:40.874 --> 05:43.942
Did, uh, any of you guys
happen to see

05:43.944 --> 05:46.611
a ghost during the party?

05:46.613 --> 05:48.947
Um, well...

05:48.949 --> 05:49.581
Life's too short!

05:49.583 --> 05:55.053
It's time to leave
this room and experience
all the wonders of the world!

05:55.055 --> 05:57.089
Honey, you are so right!

05:57.091 --> 06:00.425
I've been stuck here
for centuries.

06:00.427 --> 06:01.993
I'm taking your advice!

06:01.995 --> 06:04.396
Code rainbow!
Code rainbow!

06:04.398 --> 06:06.765
This is not a drill!

06:07.500 --> 06:08.834
(BOTH GASPING)

06:08.836 --> 06:13.905
Looks like it's time
to take out
the Trash... Mouth.

06:14.040 --> 06:17.442
I'm going to live my life!

06:20.079 --> 06:21.380
Whoopsie.

06:21.382 --> 06:22.647
So, Maggie is gone?

06:22.649 --> 06:24.683
Without my ghost writer,
I'll be ruined!

06:24.685 --> 06:28.053
I'll have
to go back to scurrying
behind refrigerators!

06:28.055 --> 06:29.254
No!

06:29.256 --> 06:31.556
(SOBBING)

06:31.824 --> 06:34.826
Man, I would not want
to be you right now.

06:34.828 --> 06:36.828
If Lydia finds out
it's all your fault

06:36.830 --> 06:41.199
that he didn't write the book
he dedicated to her... Ooh!

06:43.136 --> 06:45.904
(MIMICS EXPLOSION)
Yup, but worse.

06:45.906 --> 06:49.374
Yeah, we gotta get
that ghost back.

06:50.042 --> 06:53.412
Okay, this is not
one of my best ideas.

06:57.683 --> 07:01.219
Hey, that's not garbage...
Mostly! Give it back!

07:01.221 --> 07:03.088
To new adventures!

07:03.090 --> 07:06.458
Uh, you guys go on
without me.

07:06.460 --> 07:08.560
(SCREAMING)

07:08.562 --> 07:09.995
(BELCHING)

07:09.997 --> 07:11.663
(SCREAMING)

07:13.499 --> 07:17.903
Man, check out how big
this Trash Mouth's stomach is.

07:17.905 --> 07:20.605
Respect.
Look! There she is!

07:20.607 --> 07:23.208
(CHUCKLING)

07:23.543 --> 07:24.509
Hey, it's you!

07:24.511 --> 07:26.878
Thanks so much
for your advice!

07:26.880 --> 07:27.979
This place is great!

07:27.981 --> 07:29.881
(LAUGHING NERVOUSLY)
Yeah, it sure is.

07:29.883 --> 07:35.420
But wouldn't it be cooler
if you came back to room 1313

07:35.422 --> 07:38.490
and, oh, I don't know,
wrote another novel?

07:38.492 --> 07:39.791
Way to ease her
into it, Mavis.

07:39.793 --> 07:42.260
No way.
I'm done being a writer.

07:42.262 --> 07:45.063
Like the talking booger said,
life's too short!

07:45.065 --> 07:46.364
What did you call me?

07:46.366 --> 07:49.434
I'm never going back
to that stuffy ol' room

07:49.436 --> 07:52.037
when there's so much
to experience here!

07:52.039 --> 07:55.307
(GASPS) Look,
a garbage mound!

07:55.309 --> 07:57.609
And another one! Ooh!

07:57.611 --> 07:58.844
This is bad.

07:58.846 --> 08:01.079
There's no way Shivers is
going to have his book done

08:01.081 --> 08:02.914
by tomorrow.
Unless...

08:02.916 --> 08:05.083
A ghost writer
writes the novel!

08:05.085 --> 08:08.653
Or better yet,
a team of ghost writers!

08:08.655 --> 08:12.657
Sweet! We're gonna clone
a team of ghosts?

08:12.659 --> 08:14.860
Can we just go?

08:16.629 --> 08:18.897
Are you sure
this is Maggie?

08:18.899 --> 08:22.000
Uh, no. This is
her writing partner...

08:22.002 --> 08:24.536
Uh, ah, Sandoval.

08:24.538 --> 08:27.005
Why does Hank get
to be the ghost?

08:27.007 --> 08:27.772
Um, cause he's awesome?

08:27.774 --> 08:31.810
Don't you remember
his big run in
the <i>Lizard of Gauze?</i>

08:31.812 --> 08:35.380
I am the great
and powerful Gauze!

08:35.381 --> 08:37.982
Ahh, fire!

08:37.985 --> 08:40.385
Oh, I love
legitimate theater!

08:40.386 --> 08:42.754
(GHOSTLY MOANING)
I'm a ghost writer

08:42.756 --> 08:46.458
who's going to write you
the best book ever!

08:46.460 --> 08:47.893
(COUGHING)

08:47.895 --> 08:49.327
Oh, perfect!

08:49.329 --> 08:52.898
And just in time
for my next molt!

08:52.900 --> 08:54.332
(SNORING)

08:54.901 --> 08:56.968
Okay, chapter one.

08:56.970 --> 08:57.736
Nailed it!

08:57.738 --> 09:02.340
MAVIS: The kingdom was ruled
by the kind and generous king.

09:02.342 --> 09:03.542
(ROARING)

09:03.544 --> 09:05.210
Well, he wasn't
kind all the time.

09:05.212 --> 09:06.244
He definitely had a temper!

09:06.246 --> 09:09.748
The king's daughter was
the most popular princess
in the land.

09:09.750 --> 09:13.318
But the evil queen
didn't like her
and wanted her gone!

09:13.320 --> 09:17.355
PEDRO:
Yeah, but then the majestic
ninja warrior appeared!

09:17.357 --> 09:18.557
He was so awesome!

09:18.559 --> 09:21.927
MAVIS:
Uh, no. That's totally
unbelievable. Scrap it.

09:21.929 --> 09:23.161
Uh, let me try.

09:23.163 --> 09:25.597
It was a dark
and stormy night.

09:25.599 --> 09:28.967
The hydra appears and, uh...

09:28.969 --> 09:29.868
I got nothing.

09:29.870 --> 09:31.236
Step aside.
I got this!

09:31.238 --> 09:33.538
They have a,
wait for it...

09:33.540 --> 09:34.839
Disco dance party!

09:34.841 --> 09:37.676
<i>♪ Freak right out,</i>
<i>freak right out!</i>

09:37.678 --> 09:40.312
<i>♪ Ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh</i>

09:40.314 --> 09:43.214
Ah, we'll leave it in
because we need the pages.

09:43.216 --> 09:43.748
Oh, come on!

09:43.750 --> 09:46.918
MAVIS: So, the king and
the princess saved the day

09:46.920 --> 09:51.623
and there was nothing
the evil queen could do
to stop them!

09:52.558 --> 09:53.058
(YELPING)

09:53.060 --> 09:56.061
PEDRO: But then
the ninja warrior came
and kicked butt,

09:56.063 --> 09:58.129
and everyone wanted
his autograph!

09:58.131 --> 09:59.497
Yeah, nice try.

09:59.499 --> 10:01.566
MAVIS: "The end."

10:01.634 --> 10:03.768
This book is done-zo!

10:03.770 --> 10:06.137
Whoo-hoo!
Shh!

10:06.139 --> 10:09.341
(CORNELIUS SNORING
AND MUTTERING)

10:09.343 --> 10:11.610
(SNORING)

10:11.612 --> 10:12.978
(WEREWOLF HOWLING)

10:12.980 --> 10:14.412
Huh? What?

10:14.414 --> 10:15.780
Yes!

10:15.782 --> 10:17.749
I did it again!

10:17.751 --> 10:21.686
Time to take this hit novel
to the publishers!

10:21.688 --> 10:22.587
(MAVIS CLEARS THROAT)

10:22.589 --> 10:25.290
<i>"Mis-stakes to the Heart</i>
<i>was the worst thing</i>

10:25.292 --> 10:27.659
"I have have ever had
the misfortune to read.

10:27.661 --> 10:31.663
"It made my eyes bleed,
in a bad way." Whoa.

10:31.665 --> 10:34.065
Boy, the critics
really didn't like

10:34.067 --> 10:35.400
the new Cornelius
Shivers novel.

10:35.402 --> 10:39.638
"Why did the writer
put in an unlikable
mummy-ninja warrior

10:39.640 --> 10:40.639
"halfway through
the novel?"

10:40.641 --> 10:43.208
I added him back in when
you went to the bathroom.

10:43.210 --> 10:47.212
"I couldn't understand
why there were
so many dance parties."

10:47.214 --> 10:49.381
Well, I don't understand
what they didn't understand.

10:49.383 --> 10:51.683
<i>♪ Freak right out,</i>
<i>freak right out! ♪</i>

10:51.685 --> 10:53.418
"There's only one place
for Shivers

10:53.420 --> 10:56.488
"after a literary disaster
like this..."

10:56.490 --> 10:58.823
Don't look at me.
I'm hideous.

10:58.825 --> 11:01.459
AUNT LYDIA:
Can you believe this?

11:01.461 --> 11:02.694
"Dedicated to Lydia Dracula,

11:02.696 --> 11:07.499
"the inspiration
for the evil queen
who hates everything.

11:07.501 --> 11:09.467
"Lydia, you're the worst!"

11:09.469 --> 11:14.105
Oh! He thinks
I'm a queen!

11:14.306 --> 11:16.107
(SWOONING)

11:16.109 --> 11:19.644
I bet the ninjas were
her favorite part.

11:20.446 --> 11:22.580
(BATS SCREECHING)

11:22.582 --> 11:24.416
(WOLF HOWLING)

11:24.418 --> 11:28.219
Hey, quit hogging
the worm fries!

11:28.221 --> 11:29.254
Huh?

11:29.256 --> 11:31.122
Dude, I was using that.

11:31.124 --> 11:32.190
Key word,"was."

11:32.192 --> 11:35.160
(CLICKS TONGUE)
You guys really
gotta stop this.

11:35.162 --> 11:36.728
Stop what?

11:36.730 --> 11:38.496
This!

11:39.632 --> 11:42.267
Ow!
Sorry!

11:43.369 --> 11:44.636
(LAUGHING)

11:44.638 --> 11:47.038
<i>♪ Tap, tap, look at me go</i>

11:47.040 --> 11:47.772
(SCATTING)

11:47.774 --> 11:50.275
Not like I was
using those, either!

11:50.509 --> 11:50.942
(GRUNTS)

11:50.944 --> 11:54.479
Why do I have
to be the monster that
comes apart all the time?

11:54.481 --> 11:57.415
What I wouldn't give
to be all one piece.

11:57.417 --> 12:01.386
Huh. I had no idea
you felt that way, Hank.

12:01.388 --> 12:03.455
We promise not
to do it anymore.

12:03.457 --> 12:06.057
Yeah, man,
pinkie swear.

12:06.059 --> 12:06.825
Dude!

12:06.827 --> 12:09.194
Sorry,
I couldn't resist.

12:09.196 --> 12:12.030
Voila!
Your doughnuts.

12:12.032 --> 12:14.866
Not to complain,
but the whole point

12:14.868 --> 12:18.036
of pus sac donuts is that
the jelly is trapped

12:18.038 --> 12:19.804
on the inside of the sac.

12:19.806 --> 12:21.439
This kinda ruins the fun.

12:21.441 --> 12:24.976
Oh, really?
No problem.

12:25.478 --> 12:27.212
(ALL GASPING)

12:27.214 --> 12:30.715
Is that fun enough
for you? (SCOFFS)

12:30.717 --> 12:31.249
Huh.

12:31.251 --> 12:35.687
Maybe there is a way
to keep you from
coming apart, Hank.

12:35.689 --> 12:40.391
Okay, get all the magnets,
paper clips, and tape you can.

12:40.393 --> 12:40.892
Good call.

12:40.894 --> 12:43.094
And I'll raid
the refrigerator for
snacks while I'm at it.

12:43.096 --> 12:46.698
'Course you will.
Always taking things
that aren't yours.

12:46.700 --> 12:49.200
Didn't steal
as much as she did.

12:49.835 --> 12:51.736
(GIGGLING)

12:51.738 --> 12:53.805
(THUNDER CRASHING)

12:53.807 --> 12:54.939
You really think
this is gonna work?

12:54.941 --> 12:58.076
MAVIS:
Of course it's going to work.
Tape is really strong.

12:58.078 --> 13:03.615
Just wait until you see it!
'Kay, tilt him to the mirror.

13:03.749 --> 13:06.618
Come on!
(STRAINING)

13:08.754 --> 13:09.888
Ah!

13:09.890 --> 13:11.122
ALL: Hank!

13:11.124 --> 13:13.658
(THUNDER CRASHING)

13:15.127 --> 13:16.961
What?

13:16.963 --> 13:19.697
Hank, you're all...

13:22.501 --> 13:24.102
Hank, can you
hand me your arm?

13:24.104 --> 13:29.507
I want to poke you,
but I'm too scared
to use my own finger.

13:29.509 --> 13:32.710
Okay. Whoa!
(STRAINING)

13:32.712 --> 13:34.479
Come on, guys!

13:34.481 --> 13:36.147
(ALL STRAINING)

13:36.149 --> 13:37.649
Nothing's coming off.

13:37.651 --> 13:39.517
Holy rabies!

13:39.519 --> 13:42.387
Hank, you're a real boy!

13:42.389 --> 13:44.589
(GASPING)

13:45.124 --> 13:47.225
(STRAINING)

13:48.894 --> 13:50.795
All one piece!

13:50.797 --> 13:53.832
All one piece!
All one piece!

13:54.033 --> 13:56.267
All one piece!

13:57.236 --> 13:59.137
Hey, guys!

14:01.073 --> 14:03.575
Just cause you can't borrow
my arms to eat with anymore,

14:03.577 --> 14:07.378
doesn't mean
you shouldn't eat
at all. Take.

14:07.746 --> 14:10.682
So, how are you feeling?

14:10.850 --> 14:13.585
I feel alive! Alive!

14:13.587 --> 14:18.323
Alive like a reanimated
corpse or alive like a...

14:18.325 --> 14:21.092
(SNIFFING) Human.

14:21.094 --> 14:23.461
(ALL SCREAMING)

14:27.066 --> 14:28.399
Mmm-hmm.

14:28.401 --> 14:29.734
Okay, let's relax here.

14:29.736 --> 14:32.170
I'm sure there is
no reason to panic.

14:32.172 --> 14:37.242
Young man, it seems
you've got an acute case
of the...

14:37.244 --> 14:39.143
(HEART BEATING)

14:39.245 --> 14:40.912
...human!

14:40.914 --> 14:45.350
As I was saying, there
is one reason to panic.

14:45.352 --> 14:47.185
(GULPING)

14:47.920 --> 14:50.355
Hank, you can't leave!

14:50.357 --> 14:52.090
Aunt Lydia, please!
If he leaves,

14:52.092 --> 14:56.160
Wendy is gonna end up
a mess of slobbering
green slime on the floor.

14:56.162 --> 14:59.163
Isn't that
what she already is?

14:59.165 --> 15:00.632
True.

15:00.634 --> 15:02.667
Pedro, this is
no time for jokes.

15:02.669 --> 15:04.869
(GASPING)
You take that back!

15:04.871 --> 15:05.803
It's always time
for jokes.

15:05.805 --> 15:10.441
I appreciate the love,
guys, but this is
a hotel for monsters.

15:10.443 --> 15:12.744
Did you see them running
for their lives?

15:12.746 --> 15:14.545
Even the dead ones!

15:14.547 --> 15:16.614
(GROANING)

15:19.685 --> 15:22.020
Hank, we're your friends.

15:22.022 --> 15:24.055
You belong here with us.

15:24.057 --> 15:25.590
You'll always be
my friends,

15:25.592 --> 15:28.760
but I gotta go be with
the other humans in,

15:28.762 --> 15:33.564
um, Humantown.
Which I wanna say is in,

15:33.566 --> 15:35.033
uh, Canada?

15:35.035 --> 15:36.234
I'm gonna miss you, man.

15:36.236 --> 15:38.369
You mask my natural
stench really well.

15:38.371 --> 15:42.440
That is the nicest thing
any monster's ever said to me.

15:42.442 --> 15:45.009
Can-a-dah?

15:45.611 --> 15:47.278
<i>♪</i>

15:48.480 --> 15:52.050
<i>♪ Hank was a green monster,</i>
<i>made up of different parts</i>

15:52.052 --> 15:54.152
<i>♪ Two legs, a mouth,</i>
<i>three kidneys</i>

15:54.154 --> 15:55.353
<i>♪ A bum that let out farts</i>

15:55.355 --> 15:57.021
<i>♪ His friends were</i>
<i>always stealing</i>

15:57.023 --> 15:58.823
<i>♪ His hand, his leg,</i>
<i>his head</i>

15:58.825 --> 16:00.992
<i>♪ To pick a nose,</i>
<i>to scratch a butt</i>

16:00.994 --> 16:02.393
<i>♪ It made poor Hank see red!</i>

16:02.395 --> 16:05.396
<i>♪ Mavis tried to help Hank</i>
<i>out with an experiment</i>

16:05.398 --> 16:09.100
<i>♪ To try to keep him</i>
<i>in one piece with</i>
<i>more than ligaments</i>

16:09.102 --> 16:12.870
<i>♪ An unexpected side effect</i>
<i>is Hank's no longer green</i>

16:12.872 --> 16:14.672
<i>♪ His stitches gone,</i>
<i>he looks human</i>

16:14.674 --> 16:16.841
<i>♪ Made all</i>
<i>the monsters scream!</i>

16:16.843 --> 16:20.244
<i>♪ Bye, ay, ay,</i>
<i>ay, ay, ay, ay</i>

16:20.246 --> 16:23.047
<i>♪ Ay, ay, ay,</i>
<i>ay, ay, bye!</i>

16:23.049 --> 16:26.584
<i>♪ Now,</i>
<i>Hank's walking down the road,</i>
<i>we follow in a hearse</i>

16:26.586 --> 16:30.054
<i>♪ He's asking us to leave, but</i>
<i>we don't know how to reverse</i>

16:30.056 --> 16:33.024
<i>♪ Oh no, Now we see Donald,</i>
<i>he's taking out the trash</i>

16:33.026 --> 16:37.562
<i>♪ I hope that</i>
<i>we can stop the car or</i>
<i>we are going to crash</i>

16:37.564 --> 16:41.299
<i>♪ Bye, ay, ay,</i>
<i>ay, ay, ay...♪</i>
<i>Ah!</i>

16:42.034 --> 16:45.703
Oh, hi, hi, hi, hi,
hi to you, too!

16:45.705 --> 16:47.605
Lovely evening for a walk.

16:47.607 --> 16:49.073
Humans like to walk?

16:49.075 --> 16:51.209
(LAUGHING)
You betcha we do.

16:51.211 --> 16:55.179
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY) So,
what else do humans like?

16:55.181 --> 16:57.982
Oh, wow, we like bacon,
wearing sweatpants,

16:57.984 --> 17:00.818
smelling tennis balls,
high-fiving babies,

17:00.820 --> 17:03.454
clouds that look
like presidents!

17:04.790 --> 17:06.824
What if the humans
are horrible?

17:06.826 --> 17:08.358
The ones in Canada
may not be as nice

17:08.361 --> 17:10.795
as all the other humans
seem to think they are.

17:10.797 --> 17:13.097
Canadians are great.
And Hank'll be back!

17:13.098 --> 17:15.733
I'd say he's got about
six hours tops

17:15.734 --> 17:18.236
before he's human
for an eternity.

17:18.238 --> 17:20.471
Or however long humans live.

17:20.473 --> 17:21.105
ALL: What?

17:21.107 --> 17:25.042
Didn't I mention that?
(GRUNTS) My bad.

17:25.045 --> 17:27.512
(GROWLING)

17:28.012 --> 17:28.980
What's that?

17:28.982 --> 17:30.648
Hank has gone
to the human house?

17:30.650 --> 17:33.117
And he's talking
to them right now?

17:33.119 --> 17:34.018
(GROWLING)

17:34.020 --> 17:36.788
And you're still
in love with Fifi?

17:37.156 --> 17:38.156
(GROWLING)

17:38.158 --> 17:44.095
Ugh! I can only
solve one problem
at a time, Gavin.

17:49.034 --> 17:50.301
Oh! There he is.

17:50.303 --> 17:52.336
We have to save Hank!

17:52.338 --> 17:53.004
(MAVIS STRAINING)

17:53.006 --> 17:55.840
Sorry, Mavis,
I shouldn't have eaten
that last burrito!

17:55.842 --> 18:00.378
Of course human's
have glasses of water.
I'll get you one!

18:00.380 --> 18:02.680
Donald!
What are you thinking,

18:02.682 --> 18:04.816
chit-chatting
outside after dark?

18:04.818 --> 18:08.086
You're going
to get this poor boy
devoured by monsters

18:08.088 --> 18:11.422
and then we'll have
to cancel game night!

18:11.424 --> 18:13.724
Come on in, hun.
Join us!

18:13.726 --> 18:15.093
Adventure will be
there tomorrow,

18:15.095 --> 18:20.364
but Cartwright family
game night
only lasts for tonight!

18:20.366 --> 18:21.866
(CLAPPING)

18:21.868 --> 18:24.869
(GASPING)
I'm not afraid of fire?

18:24.871 --> 18:27.505
Uh, I mean,
you like games?

18:27.507 --> 18:31.242
Almost as much as we like
popping bubble wrap.

18:31.244 --> 18:33.644
And kitten sweaters!

18:33.646 --> 18:34.979
It's so soft.

18:34.981 --> 18:36.848
(WHISPERS) I know.

18:37.616 --> 18:39.016
(COOING)
Arr!

18:39.018 --> 18:41.853
Walk the plank,
matey! Arr!

18:41.855 --> 18:45.623
Ah, my name's Hank,
and I love being human!

18:45.625 --> 18:47.024
Of course you do!

18:47.026 --> 18:49.494
(ALL LAUGHING)

18:49.828 --> 18:52.663
Who's ready for
some hangman?

18:52.665 --> 18:54.198
I'll dig the hole.

18:54.200 --> 18:57.401
(CHUCKLES)
I don't know.

18:59.705 --> 19:01.272
(LAUGHING)

19:02.841 --> 19:04.575
(LAUGHING)

19:04.577 --> 19:07.778
Hank really is
becoming human.

19:07.780 --> 19:10.314
Can you please pass me
the sugar from up there?

19:10.316 --> 19:13.184
Sure! I'll knock it down
with my head.

19:13.186 --> 19:14.986
(STRAINING)

19:14.988 --> 19:15.653
(COOING)

19:15.655 --> 19:18.055
DONALD: Aw, she's
trying to dance!

19:18.057 --> 19:20.391
Oopsie!
Baby go boom boom?

19:20.393 --> 19:22.126
Ah, here,
use my feet.

19:22.128 --> 19:24.228
They're way better
than yours.

19:24.230 --> 19:26.464
(STRAINING)

19:28.167 --> 19:29.734
Know what this
human could use?

19:29.736 --> 19:33.070
A back scratcher.
This sweater sure is itchy!

19:33.072 --> 19:36.841
Here. Borrow my arm.
(STRAINING)

19:37.576 --> 19:40.011
It won't come off.

19:43.382 --> 19:44.882
Oh, yes!

19:44.884 --> 19:46.884
(CHUCKLING) Yeah.

19:46.886 --> 19:48.586
<i>♪</i>

19:55.327 --> 19:58.563
I miss my friends.
I miss my old life.

19:58.565 --> 20:00.765
Even my scars are fading.

20:00.767 --> 20:03.267
Wait, my scars are fading?

20:03.269 --> 20:05.102
Like going away?

20:05.104 --> 20:08.005
So, I won't still
be a monster?

20:08.007 --> 20:10.608
(SCREAMING)
I gotta go!

20:10.742 --> 20:12.009
Ah! Wait!

20:12.011 --> 20:16.247
Go? But there are
(STUTTERS) monsters
out there!

20:16.249 --> 20:19.217
HANK: Yes!
There are monsters outside!

20:19.219 --> 20:23.754
DONALD:
And we've got more popcorn.
So, much popcorn!

20:23.756 --> 20:25.957
HANK:
Ah, what's popcorn?

20:25.959 --> 20:29.560
Ooh, it's yummy,
try some!

20:29.562 --> 20:31.696
WENDY: Hank's scars
are almost gone!

20:31.698 --> 20:34.398
How do we get him
outta there?

20:34.400 --> 20:36.467
(THUNDER CRASHING)

20:36.469 --> 20:37.235
I have an idea.

20:37.237 --> 20:40.304
Does it involve getting
out of the rain?

20:40.306 --> 20:41.105
No, sir!

20:41.107 --> 20:43.274
Now, all we have to do
is work backward

20:43.276 --> 20:48.579
from the moment
Hank got zapped and
turned into a real boy!

20:48.581 --> 20:50.448
So, if Hank is in the house,

20:50.450 --> 20:51.983
and the house
is struck by lightning,

20:51.985 --> 20:53.951
then everything should
go back to normal

20:53.953 --> 20:56.587
because... Science!
You sure about this?

20:56.589 --> 21:00.391
Of course! Okay, technically,
I have no clue what I'm doing,

21:00.393 --> 21:01.158
but my dad always says...

21:01.160 --> 21:02.693
(IN DRACULA'S VOICE)
"Be confident and you can

21:02.695 --> 21:04.528
"fake your way
through anything!"

21:04.530 --> 21:06.964
(MUFFLED)
I so never said that.

21:06.966 --> 21:11.002
He says,
"I so never said that."

21:11.136 --> 21:12.803
Be right bat!

21:12.805 --> 21:15.273
Hold this metal thingy!

21:17.276 --> 21:21.012
Oh! Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

21:22.080 --> 21:24.715
(GIGGLING) Yes!

21:29.421 --> 21:34.058
Okay, don't be afraid,
it's just...

21:34.060 --> 21:35.660
(SCREAMING)
(SCREAMING)

21:35.662 --> 21:38.095
BOTH: Monsters!

21:38.097 --> 21:38.963
Fire!

21:38.965 --> 21:41.565
Fire! Fire!
Fire, fire, fire!

21:41.567 --> 21:44.368
Fire! Hey,
I'm afraid of fire!

21:44.370 --> 21:46.070
Ah! Fire!

21:46.705 --> 21:48.139
(CRASHING)

21:48.141 --> 21:51.575
Ow! I'm back, baby!

21:52.644 --> 21:55.780
Man, do I feel good!

21:55.782 --> 21:59.016
Hey, wait.
What are these?

21:59.018 --> 22:00.151
Not funny, guys.

22:00.153 --> 22:02.186
Whoops!
Nope, still not funny.

22:02.188 --> 22:05.423
(ALL LAUGHING)
Really, not that funny.

22:06.224 --> 22:08.092
<i>♪</i>
